			{"text": "Shortly after Bulvan's defeat, Zorgorath speeds up his plan and sends the giants of Erhab to attack Dwargon, and sends the trolls to attack Nevdes. In the swift attack, Nevdes was defeated, as most of Nevdes' troops joined the Aeyris Alliances in the war against Bulvan. Zorgorath ordered Ttarmek to open the Endless Door in one of the dungeons of Nevdes, one of which is connected to the Slumbering Gate, so that Zorgorath could send more troops there. Opposing the chances of Zorgorath ruling the world, Barret, king of Malus, declared war against the trolls and marched to the southeast to cancel the operation. Despite the Malusian efforts, Ttarmek and his army of trolls managed to defend the conquered city."},
			{"separator": true},
			{"text": "Tips to play:"},
			{"text": "Immediately contruct Workers to improve Hill or or mined resources, this will increase your city's [Production] faster than other civs."},
			{"text": "it's uniques and Ramming Troll are a perfect combination to attack cities."}
		]
	},
	
